other_tests.findings: Mild hemodynamic instability suggestive of carotid sinus hypersensitivity (CSH) occurred after the second embolization.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The patient experienced transient episodes of bradycardia and hypotension during the night after the second embolization, which resolved with medical management.

other_tests.findings: The patient became asystolic during surgery and required resuscitation, leading to the placement of a temporary pacemaker.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Following the implantation of the pacemaker, the patient remained stable and did not have further episodes of bradycardia.

other_tests.findings: Did not show any signs of cardiac ischemia or primary heart blockage.
